p: There was no significant difference in the amount of RNA (transformed by y = log 10) detected in Cx. tarsalis infected bodies following competition, except for isolate KERN-07-291 which replicated less efficiently (P = 0.006) in co-infected bodies compared to COAV997-5nt ( Fig 2C). However, despite replicating to higher RNA copies in Cx. tarsalis bodies, COAV997-5nt was not transmitted at a significantly higher rate (P>0.05) compared to isolate KERN-07-291 ( Fig 1B).
